                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12828: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-04T22:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 4, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 4—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>930. The Soviet Ambassador came to the Embassy today by appointment to express
                    his felicitations on Independence Day. He said that in his recent talk with the
                    Foreign Minister, Mr. Matsuoka had stated that Japan is in a very delicate and
                    difficult position; that there would be no alteration in Japan’s policy for the
                    present but that if circumstances should change, Japan’s policy might also
                    change. According to the Ambassador, the Minister for Foreign Affairs made no
                    allusion to the Japanese-Soviet neutrality treaty except that he “remembered
                    it.” The Ambassador characterized Mr. Matsuoka’s foregoing statement as “very
                    strange.”</p>
                <p>It is understood that the ladies of the Soviet Embassy are leaving for Russia
                    tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
